<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
With pale brownish dorsal colouration and faint indications of black tipped elytral apices, aedeagal sheath pattern and aedeagus very similar to that of 
<emphasis box="[727,874,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName box="[776,874,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
from which it is most obviously distinguished by the dorsal colouration. The molecular phylogeny (
<figureCitation box="[737,807,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,870,892]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,198,845]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,193,849]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbour Joining bootstrap consensus tree of several aquatic fireflies in South East Asia, with firefly Pyrocoelia pectoralis as outgroup." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257998/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) suggested 
<emphasis box="[949,1089,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName box="[949,1049,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Sclerotia</taxonomicName>
fui
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1188,223,248]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">sp. nov</emphasis>
. is distinct from 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,249,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis" status="comb. nov.">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[256,384,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[256,377,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Male</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[276,414,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="8.1" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="9.4" valueMin="8.1">8.1–9.4 mm</quantity>
long, width/length 0.4. Colour: pronotum orange yellow, irregular retraction of fat body material in certain areas makes these areas appear darker; MS and MN yellow; elytra very light brown with small dark brown area at apex in dry pinned specimens, semitransparent with dark hind wing visible in ethanol preserved specimens (
<figureCitation box="[288,376,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 − 96" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[212,1327,243,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[212,1374,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 93 − 96. Scl. flavida male (93, 94) and female (95, 96) Mt Bawangling, preserved in 70 % ethanol (NHMHAU). 93, 95 dorsal; 94, 96 ventral. Scale line is 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258011/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
); lateral margin paler yellow, semitransparent; sutural margin appearing paler as fat body material is irregularly scattered along the length, and this margin may not be white all along its length. Head dark brown, reddish brown above antennae and narrowly very pale brown immediately above antennae; antennae dark brown with anterior face of scape paler brown; labrum yellow; apices of palpi dark brown; ventral surface of body, and all legs yellow except for: dark brown tibiae and tarsi 1, tarsi 2 and posterior face of tibiae 2, tarsi 3, and pale brown posterior face of tibiae 3; posterior 1/3 of 
<date box="[697,738,583,608]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">V 5</date>
dark brown; dorsal abdomen pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Pronotum: W/L 1.7–2.1; L/BL 0.14–0.18; W/GHW 1.3–1.6. Elytron: 0.8−0.9 as long as total body length. Head: SIW/GHW 0.19; apical labial palpomeres with&gt;3 teeth. Abdomen: LO in 
<date box="[1108,1142,656,679]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">V7</date>
with wide and relatively shallow emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagal sheath sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[501,664,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 103−107</figureCitation>
): Very similar to 
<emphasis box="[862,1010,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Scl. 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1010,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis">aquatilis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; ventral sclerite roughly triangular in outline with rounded distal end (
<figureCitation box="[521,618,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
); margins not thickened; anterolateral corners acute; right sclerite (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) with transverse projection apically acute and reaching across most of the entire portion of T8; right sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[159,255,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) with three projections to the right, the posterior one apically acute, the median slender apically rounded and inclining dorsolaterally, and the third, longest projection, inclining ventrolaterally with a rounded hollow apex and arising in an emargination between the other two; left sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[933,1095,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 104−106</figureCitation>
) with three arms, all apically rounded, with anterior arm expanded, rounded and hollow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[405,571,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 101, 102</figureCitation>
): sternite with oblique bar, and slightly off centred small median posterior emargination (
<figureCitation box="[313,412,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
); median anterior margin of sheath tergite emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1140,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[326,488,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 − 110" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[231,1372,203,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[214,1386,203,1842]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 101 − 110. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males. 101, 102 aedeagal sheath dorsal (101, tergite emargination arrowed) and ventral (102 arrows indicate extent of oblique bar on sternite); 103 ventral tergite 8 with right and left sclerites; 104 − 106 left sclerite with hollowed anterior projection inclining left towards foot of page (104), right of page (105) and inclining right towards foot of page (106); 107 ventral sclerite anterior margin to foot of page; 108 − 110 aedeagus left ventrolateral (108), left lateral (109) and slightly dorsolateral (110). Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 101, 102; 104 − 106; 108, 110." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258013/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 108−110</figureCitation>
): L/ 
<geoCoordinate box="[534,605,1052,1076]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" precision="5555" value="-2.1">W 2.1</geoCoordinate>
−2.3. LL of unequal length (left slightly shorter than right); apices of LL rounded with inner apical margins toothed. Length basal piece/total length aedeagus 0.4−0.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" box="[199,1072,1124,1149]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1124,1149]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Female</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[308,449,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 − 100" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[341,1279,506,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[260,1327,485,1945]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 97 − 100. Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype male (97, 98) and female (99, 100) fresh collection Honghu City (NHMHAU). 97, 99 dorsal; 98, 100 ventral. Scale line is 5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258012/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Figs 99, 100</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[465,600,1124,1148]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="8.8" valueMax="9.4" valueMin="8.2">8.2–9.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[670,805,1124,1149]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="3.45" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.6 mm</quantity>
wide; width/length 0.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1184]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species named for Xin Hua Fu who first observed and studied this backswimmer firefly in mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[262,333,1196,1221]" name="China" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,151,1509]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1256]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been misidentified as 
<taxonomicName box="[763,969,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis box="[763,969,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several publications. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1246,1436,1231,1256]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Fu, X. H., Ohba, N., Vencl, F. V. &amp; Lei, C. L. (2005 a) Structure, behavior and the life cycle of an aquatic firefly, Luciola substriata (Coleoptera: Lampyridae), in China. The Canadian Entomologist, 137, 83 - 90." type="journal article">
Fu 
<emphasis box="[1284,1341,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
(2005a)
</bibRefCitation>
reported on the biology of an aquatic firefly from 
<collectingRegion box="[746,925,1268,1293]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
which they identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham" authorityName="Gorham" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis box="[1227,1436,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
Gorham
</taxonomicName>
, a first record of the species from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[734,805,1303,1328]" name="China" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[815,1002,1303,1328]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Fu, X. H., Wang, Y. &amp; Lei, C. (2005 b) The swimming behaviour of theaquatic larvae of the firefly Luciola substriata (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 50 (4), 501 - 505." type="journal article">
Fu 
<emphasis box="[851,907,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
(2005b)
</bibRefCitation>
reported on the swimming behavior of the aquatic larvae of the firefly 
<taxonomicName box="[538,749,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis box="[538,749,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Their identification was based on Obha’s comparison of specimens with those already recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[669,751,1375,1400]" name="Taiwan" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[799,1005,1375,1401]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Jeng, M. L, Lai, J. &amp; Yang, P. S. (2003) Lampyridae: A synopsis of aquatic fireflies with description of a new species (Coleoptera). In: Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (Eds.). Water Beetles of China. Volume III. Zoologisch-Botanische Gesellschaft in Asterreichand wiener Coleopterologenverein. Vienna, Austria, pp. 539 - 562." type="book chapter">
Jeng 
<emphasis box="[860,919,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1019,1202,1375,1400]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Fu, X. H. &amp; Ballantyne, L. A. (2009) Chapter 12: Larval respiration system and evolution in aquatic fireflies (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). In: Victor Benno Meyer- Rochow (Ed.), Bioluminescence in Focus - A Collection of Illuminating Essays. Research Signpost, Kerala, India." type="book">
Fu 
<emphasis box="[1059,1110,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
described the larval respiration system in a species they identified as 
<emphasis box="[731,947,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName box="[731,944,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">Luciola substriata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne" box="[958,1304,1412,1437]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Zootaxa, 1997, 1 - 188." type="journal article" year="2009">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin (2009</bibRefCitation>
, 2013) and 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,416,1447,1472]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Ballantyne, L. A., Lambkin, C. L., Boontop, Y. &amp; Jusoh, W. F. A. (2015) Revisional studies on the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae): 1. The firefly genus Pyrophanes Olivier. 2. Four new species of Pteroptyx Olivier. 3. Inflata gen. nov. Boontop. Zootaxa, 3959 (1), 1 - 84. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3959.1.1" type="journal article">
Ballantyne 
<emphasis box="[279,328,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
scored this species as ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[670,783,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">substriata</taxonomicName>
Fu’. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fu" box="[842,995,1448,1472]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" refString="Fu, X. H. (2014) An illustrated handbook of Chinese fireflies. The Commercial Press. 167 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2014">Fu (2014: 33)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated this species including larvae as 
<taxonomicName box="[181,386,1484,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriata">
<emphasis box="[181,386,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Luciola substriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
